 {"id": "bd-66l", "title": "EPIC: Hard Quality Gates and CI Enforcement", "description": "Background:
The plan defines non-negotiable gates. They must be automated and enforced to prevent regressions from entering mainline.

Goal:
Encode all required gates in CI with reproducible artifacts and clear fail reasons.

Gates include:
- portability, OOM semantics, fuzz parity
- embedded matrix, profile parity, semantic-delta budget
- HFT tail/jitter, automotive deadline/watchdog
- crash/restart replay continuity
- warning/static-analysis/bounded-proof gates

Why this serves users:
- transforms policy into enforceable guarantees
- makes trust scalable beyond individual reviewers.

Cross-cutting quality contract:
- Child tasks must define and link unit tests, e2e script coverage (when behavioral), and structured log/manifest artifacts or explicit rationale for non-applicability.
- Completion evidence must remain compatible with bd-66l.9 enforcement and traceability index expectations.", "notes": "Executed API ergonomics validation lane work (bd-56t.5 content) under this quality-gate epic: added make test-vignettes target, CI step+manifest wiring, tests/TEST.md vignette coverage docs, docs/API_ERGONOMICS_VALIDATION.md sign-off, and fixed vignette compile/runtime issues. Validation via rch: make test-vignettes/build/format-check/lint/test pass. Conformance now runs under rch with SEMANTIC_DELTA_ARTIFACT_DIR override support in tools/ci/run_conformance.sh; current remote conformance still fails on existing non-budgetable semantic-delta condition (fail=1, diff_records=1), not a permission failure.", "status": "closed", "priority": 0, "issue_type": "epic", "assignee": "IvoryGlacier", "created_at": "2026-02-27T00:47:42.390018086Z", "created_by": "ubuntu", "updated_at": "2026-03-01T05:30:49.559586930Z", "closed_at": "2026-03-01T05:30:49.559560691Z", "close_reason": "done", "source_repo": ".", "compaction_level": 0, "original_size": 0, "labels": ["ci", "phase-10", "quality-gates"], "dependencies": [{"issue_id": "bd-66l", "depends_on_id": "bd-1md", "type": "blocks", "created_at": "2026-03-02T04:37:11Z", "created_by": "import", "metadata": "{}", "thread_id": ""}, {"issue_id": "bd-66l", "depends_on_id": "bd-296", "type": "blocks", "created_at": "2026-03-02T04:37:11Z", "created_by": "import", "metadata": "{}", "thread_id": ""}, {"issue_id": "bd-66l", "depends_on_id": "bd-2cw", "type": "blocks", "created_at": "2026-03-02T04:37:11Z", "created_by": "import", "metadata": "{}", "thread_id": ""}, {"issue_id": "bd-66l", "depends_on_id": "bd-2n0", "type": "blocks", "created_at": "2026-03-02T04:37:11Z", "created_by": "import", "metadata": "{}", "thread_id": ""}, {"issue_id": "bd-66l", "depends_on_id": "bd-hwb", "type": "blocks", "created_at": "2026-03-02T04:37:11Z", "created_by": "import", "metadata": "{}", "thread_id": ""}, {"issue_id": "bd-66l", "depends_on_i